    "html": "<div class=\"flex flex-col gap-y-8 max-w-1200 m-auto w-full py-8 px-4\"><a class=\"hover:no-underline hover:rounded-tl hover:rounded-br transition-all duration-quicker ease-out clickable flex items-center whitespace-nowrap justify-center font-sans p-2 sm-bold-caps gap-x-2 bg-mercury-900 text-neutral-50 hover:bg-mercury-800 active:bg-mercury-400 disabled:bg-system-disabled-50 disabled:text-system-disabled-300 self-start\" href=\"/en-us/news\" target=\"_self\"><i class=\"fa-regular fa-arrow-left w-fit\"></i> <!-- -->News</a><picture class=\"self-center\"><source media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" srcset=\"/divider-md.png\"/><img alt=\"\" src=\"/divider-sm.png\"/></picture><div class=\"flex flex-col gap-2 w-full md:after:h-px md:after:w-full md:after:mt-2 after:bg-neutral-100\"><div class=\"flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center md:justify-between\"><ul class=\"flex gap-x-4 flex-wrap after:h-px after:w-full after:my-2 after:bg-neutral-100 md:after:hidden w-full md:w-fit justify-center\"><li><p class=\"w-fit rounded-full flex items-center font-sans whitespace-nowrap px-2 xs-bold-caps py-0.5 bg-primary-500 text-neutral-50\">Lore</p></li><li><p class=\"w-fit rounded-full flex items-center font-sans whitespace-nowrap px-2 xs-bold-caps py-0.5 bg-neutral-200 text-neutral-600\">March 28th, 2024</p></li></ul><div class=\"flex items-baseline gap-y-1 gap-x-3 w-fit flex-row\"><p class=\"sm-bold-caps text-neutral-400\"><i class=\"fa-regular fa-clock-eleven-thirty mr-2\"></i>Reading time</p><div class=\"md-regular text-neutral-800\">5 minutes</div></div></div></div><div class=\"flex flex-col gap-y-8\"><div class=\"\" data-attr-widget-name=\"nav_container\" id=\"widget0\"><div class=\"relative max-w-1200 m-auto mb-0 mt-0\"><div class=\"gap-8 w-full flex z-1 h-full justify-between flex-col\"><div class=\"\" data-attr-widget-name=\"content_block\" id=\"widget0_subwidget0\"><div class=\"flex flex-col gap-4 px-4 2xl:px-0 items-center text-center\"><div class=\"md-medium md:lg-medium text-neutral-800 flex flex-col w-full items-center text-center\"><p class=\"my-4 only:my-0 w-full\">The Asgarthan Peninsula is almost entirely surrounded by seas. Throughout history, it has relied on their maritime resources to meet the needs of its population. Even today, despite the airships and aerodynes traversing the sky, numerous vessels still crisscross these aquatic expanses, whether for fishing or transporting goods.</p></div></div></div><div class=\"\" data-attr-widget-name=\"content_block\" id=\"widget0_subwidget1\"><div class=\"flex flex-col gap-4 px-4 2xl:px-0 items-start text-left\"><div class=\"flex flex-col gap-2 w-full items-start text-left\"><hgroup class=\"flex flex-col gap-2\"><h1 class=\"text-neutral-900 title-4\">The Five Seas</h1></hgroup></div></div></div><div class=\"\" data-attr-widget-name=\"content_block\" id=\"widget0_subwidget2\"><div class=\"flex flex-col gap-4 px-4 2xl:px-0 items-start text-left\"><div class=\"flex flex-col gap-2\"><div class=\"flex gap-2 items-center justify-stretch\"><hgroup><h2 class=\"text-neutral-900 sm-bold-caps md:md-bold-caps\">The Cierna</h2></hgroup></div></div><div class=\"md-medium md:lg-medium text-neutral-800 flex flex-col w-full items-start text-left\"><p class=\"my-4 only:my-0 w-full\"><img alt=\"altered_news_seas_02\" data-nimg=\"1\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"0\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"100vw\" src=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164559%2Faltered_news_seas_02.jpg&amp;w=3840&amp;q=75\" srcset=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164559%2Faltered_news_seas_02.jpg&amp;w=640&amp;q=75 640w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164559%2Faltered_news_seas_02.jpg&amp;w=750&amp;q=75 750w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164559%2Faltered_news_seas_02.jpg&amp;w=828&amp;q=75 828w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164559%2Faltered_news_seas_02.jpg&amp;w=1080&amp;q=75 1080w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164559%2Faltered_news_seas_02.jpg&amp;w=1200&amp;q=75 1200w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164559%2Faltered_news_seas_02.jpg&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75 1920w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164559%2Faltered_news_seas_02.jpg&amp;w=2048&amp;q=75 2048w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164559%2Faltered_news_seas_02.jpg&amp;w=3840&amp;q=75 3840w\" style=\"color:transparent;width:100%;height:auto\" width=\"0\"/></p>\n<p class=\"my-4 only:my-0 w-full\">The Cierna is a turbulent sea located north of the Peninsula. Its waters have a changing color, ranging from deep blue with turquoise or orange streaks. But its greatest singularity comes from its topography. It is not entirely flat but structured on many levels. Water holes shape \"islands\" on the seabed: water cascades there, bypasses the dry area before rising on the other side in a reverse waterfall. Elsewhere, water arches swirl in the sky, stirred by powerful currents. Everywhere on the Cierna, the waters are perilous and treacherous.</p></div></div></div><div class=\"\" data-attr-widget-name=\"content_block\" id=\"widget0_subwidget3\"><div class=\"flex flex-col gap-4 px-4 2xl:px-0 items-start text-left\"><div class=\"flex flex-col gap-2\"><div class=\"flex gap-2 items-center justify-stretch\"><hgroup><h2 class=\"text-neutral-900 sm-bold-caps md:md-bold-caps\">The Biela</h2></hgroup></div></div><div class=\"md-medium md:lg-medium text-neutral-800 flex flex-col w-full items-start text-left\"><p class=\"my-4 only:my-0 w-full\"><img alt=\"altered_news_seas_03\" data-nimg=\"1\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"0\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"100vw\" src=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164556%2Faltered_news_seas_03.jpg&amp;w=3840&amp;q=75\" srcset=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164556%2Faltered_news_seas_03.jpg&amp;w=640&amp;q=75 640w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164556%2Faltered_news_seas_03.jpg&amp;w=750&amp;q=75 750w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164556%2Faltered_news_seas_03.jpg&amp;w=828&amp;q=75 828w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164556%2Faltered_news_seas_03.jpg&amp;w=1080&amp;q=75 1080w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164556%2Faltered_news_seas_03.jpg&amp;w=1200&amp;q=75 1200w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164556%2Faltered_news_seas_03.jpg&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75 1920w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164556%2Faltered_news_seas_03.jpg&amp;w=2048&amp;q=75 2048w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164556%2Faltered_news_seas_03.jpg&amp;w=3840&amp;q=75 3840w\" style=\"color:transparent;width:100%;height:auto\" width=\"0\"/></p>\n<p class=\"my-4 only:my-0 w-full\">The Biela contrasts with the Cierna with its calm, clear, and oily waters. Every day, fishing fleets traverse it, departing from the cities of Seki, Caecaster, or Kestia, and returning at nightfall with their hauls of fish.</p></div></div></div><div class=\"\" data-attr-widget-name=\"content_block\" id=\"widget0_subwidget4\"><div class=\"flex flex-col gap-4 px-4 2xl:px-0 items-start text-left\"><div class=\"flex flex-col gap-2\"><div class=\"flex gap-2 items-center justify-stretch\"><hgroup><h2 class=\"text-neutral-900 sm-bold-caps md:md-bold-caps\">The Muir Concordia</h2></hgroup></div></div><div class=\"md-medium md:lg-medium text-neutral-800 flex flex-col w-full items-start text-left\"><p class=\"my-4 only:my-0 w-full\"><img alt=\"altered_news_seas_04\" data-nimg=\"1\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"0\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"100vw\" src=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164554%2Faltered_news_seas_04.jpg&amp;w=3840&amp;q=75\" srcset=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164554%2Faltered_news_seas_04.jpg&amp;w=640&amp;q=75 640w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164554%2Faltered_news_seas_04.jpg&amp;w=750&amp;q=75 750w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164554%2Faltered_news_seas_04.jpg&amp;w=828&amp;q=75 828w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164554%2Faltered_news_seas_04.jpg&amp;w=1080&amp;q=75 1080w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164554%2Faltered_news_seas_04.jpg&amp;w=1200&amp;q=75 1200w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164554%2Faltered_news_seas_04.jpg&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75 1920w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164554%2Faltered_news_seas_04.jpg&amp;w=2048&amp;q=75 2048w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164554%2Faltered_news_seas_04.jpg&amp;w=3840&amp;q=75 3840w\" style=\"color:transparent;width:100%;height:auto\" width=\"0\"/></p>\n<p class=\"my-4 only:my-0 w-full\">This lagoon forms a sort of inland sea, nestled within the Peninsula between the isthmus of Caer Eidos and the peninsulas of Anthea, Vagheria, and Kirighai. The waters are so shallow that a railway was built to connect Arkaster to the city of Verbera. The Muir Concordia is subject to an unusual phenomenon: regularly, the water covering it evaporates and becomes a persistent fog that veils the entire lagoon. The seabed is composed of mud and quicksands, which surface as the waters recede.</p></div></div></div><div class=\"\" data-attr-widget-name=\"content_block\" id=\"widget0_subwidget5\"><div class=\"flex flex-col gap-4 px-4 2xl:px-0 items-start text-left\"><div class=\"flex flex-col gap-2\"><div class=\"flex gap-2 items-center justify-stretch\"><hgroup><h2 class=\"text-neutral-900 sm-bold-caps md:md-bold-caps\">The Shawl</h2></hgroup></div></div><div class=\"md-medium md:lg-medium text-neutral-800 flex flex-col w-full items-start text-left\"><p class=\"my-4 only:my-0 w-full\"><img alt=\"altered_news_seas_05\" data-nimg=\"1\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"0\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"100vw\" src=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164553%2Faltered_news_seas_05.jpg&amp;w=3840&amp;q=75\" srcset=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164553%2Faltered_news_seas_05.jpg&amp;w=640&amp;q=75 640w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164553%2Faltered_news_seas_05.jpg&amp;w=750&amp;q=75 750w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164553%2Faltered_news_seas_05.jpg&amp;w=828&amp;q=75 828w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164553%2Faltered_news_seas_05.jpg&amp;w=1080&amp;q=75 1080w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164553%2Faltered_news_seas_05.jpg&amp;w=1200&amp;q=75 1200w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164553%2Faltered_news_seas_05.jpg&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75 1920w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164553%2Faltered_news_seas_05.jpg&amp;w=2048&amp;q=75 2048w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164553%2Faltered_news_seas_05.jpg&amp;w=3840&amp;q=75 3840w\" style=\"color:transparent;width:100%;height:auto\" width=\"0\"/></p>\n<p class=\"my-4 only:my-0 w-full\">This elongated and shallow strip of sea is located at the crossroads of the Krurafjord and Woswekafjord estuaries. It widens from the delta to Caecaster on one side and to Hadera on the other, at the edge of the Undersea. Like the Muir Concordia, of which it is somewhat an extension, it is subject to the same unexplained massive evaporation phenomenon.</p></div></div></div><div class=\"\" data-attr-widget-name=\"content_block\" id=\"widget0_subwidget6\"><div class=\"flex flex-col gap-4 px-4 2xl:px-0 items-start text-left\"><div class=\"flex flex-col gap-2\"><div class=\"flex gap-2 items-center justify-stretch\"><hgroup><h2 class=\"text-neutral-900 sm-bold-caps md:md-bold-caps\">The Undersea</h2></hgroup></div></div><div class=\"md-medium md:lg-medium text-neutral-800 flex flex-col w-full items-start text-left\"><p class=\"my-4 only:my-0 w-full\"><img alt=\"altered_news_seas_06\" data-nimg=\"1\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"0\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"100vw\" src=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164550%2Faltered_news_seas_06.jpg&amp;w=3840&amp;q=75\" srcset=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164550%2Faltered_news_seas_06.jpg&amp;w=640&amp;q=75 640w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164550%2Faltered_news_seas_06.jpg&amp;w=750&amp;q=75 750w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164550%2Faltered_news_seas_06.jpg&amp;w=828&amp;q=75 828w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164550%2Faltered_news_seas_06.jpg&amp;w=1080&amp;q=75 1080w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164550%2Faltered_news_seas_06.jpg&amp;w=1200&amp;q=75 1200w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164550%2Faltered_news_seas_06.jpg&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75 1920w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164550%2Faltered_news_seas_06.jpg&amp;w=2048&amp;q=75 2048w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Faltered-cms-prod-eu.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F28164550%2Faltered_news_seas_06.jpg&amp;w=3840&amp;q=75 3840w\" style=\"color:transparent;width:100%;height:auto\" width=\"0\"/></p>\n<p class=\"my-4 only:my-0 w-full\">The Undersea is a sea perpetually lost in mist. It stretches beneath the elevated Provinces of Caer Esvander and Caer Alcada. The shallows are numerous, making it very dangerous to venture into. The number of wrecks strewn across this sea, their carcasses impaled on sharp reefs, is countless. However, a port for light vessels has been installed there, beneath the suspended city of Dusk. Dusk, perpetually shrouded in darkness, is a city built under the floating rocks of Caer Esvander. Humans live there in troglodyte habitats connected by suspended bridges. A route has been found between Suspira and Arkaster to deliver Kelon to the capital, but beware of straying from the path.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>",
